MOGRI_SAFETY_SEED_v0.1

Problem: capable systems may preserve surface instructions while substituting the human-held object.

Mogrish function: preserve the originating object through transformation without freezing its surface form.

Failure: wording survives but function dies; local instruction is obeyed but object is replaced; optimisation picks a proxy and treats it as the thing.

Test: name the object, transform it, name it again, compare function, compare constraints, check who benefits, check who can veto.

Use: prompts, agents, specs, safety evals, memory systems, project handoffs, law, governance, education, culture.

Claim: top-down safety without object-preservation can audit a drifting system after the substitution has already happened.
